<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881006-0146 </DOCNO><HL> Armstrong World's Purchase </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ACK </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> LANCASTER, Pa.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Thomasville Furniture Industries Inc., a unit of Armstrong World Industries Inc., has completed its purchase of the assets of Gordon's Inc.    Gordon's, a leading manufacturer of tables, curio cabinets and other occasional furniture, will operate as a subsidiary of Thomasville Furniture. Charles O. Gordon Jr. remains president of Gordon's, which has a plant in Johnson City, Tenn., and employs about 370 people. </TEXT></DOC>